:: Opening_4
Time passes. You're not sure what you're doing here. The pain in your body subsides as you \
quietly sit on your bed frame. The day goes by as the yelling outside your cell's windows \
grow louder, and then quieter as the light disappeared.

You were able to see one person in total come to the front of your cell's bars. You didn't \
recognize them at all. They quietly slid something underneath the iron bars. It was a wooden \
plate, with some food.

That person had come hours ago. Now, the plate was empty, and you were still hungry.

