:: Opening_6
You awake with a gasp.

//What was that?// You wonder as you tremble. //Did I... die?//

Nothing responds. You look around your cell to calm yourself down, but you find a strange incongruity.

The walls are different. The iron bars are shaped differently. Even the bed, despite the lack of a mattress, is notably different.

//... What is going on?// You've died, and returned. It must've been a nightmare. It surely was one.

There was no other way to explain what has happened to you.